{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φρῑκ-η</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>shuddering, shivering,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 5.61 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; a mild form of ῥῖγος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Morb.” 1.24, +others\">Refs</a>]: <b>cold fit</b> before fever, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 251a (_metaphorically_, [prev. author] “R.” 387c), 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Igne” 74, 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Theriaca” 721; φρ (ε) ίκη καὶ πυρετός “IG” 3.1424.19 (Tab.Defix.), 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.27: _plural_, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 863b21. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>shivering fear, shuddering,</b> especially from religious <b>awe,</b> φρίκης αὐτὸν ὑπελθούσης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.134; τοίαν φ. παρέχεις μοι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1306 (_anapaest meter_); ὀρθόκερως φ. [prev. author] “fragment” 875, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.2.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>shivering fear</b> of any kind, <b>horror,</b> φρίκᾳ τρομερὰν φρένα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1284 (Lyric poetry); ἐκπληχθεῖσα φρίκᾳ [prev. author] “Tr.” 183 (Lyric poetry); φρίκᾳ ματρός [prev. author] “Ion” 898 (Lyric poetry); μεγάλην ἐμποιεῖ φ. 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.19 W.; ἀγωνία καὶ φ. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marius” 43; φ. καὶ φόβος [prev. author] “Pel.” 27; φ. καὶ δέος 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>ad Them.</b> 253b; φρίκῃ καὶ σιωπῇ κατεχόμενον τὸ θέατρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marcellus” 20. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> ={φρίξ}[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1, ἀκύματος πορθμὸς ἐν φρίκῃ γελᾷ “Tragica Adespota” 336; ἐν γαλήνῃ φρίκης ὑποτρεχούσης 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.921f; τὴν θάλατταν φ. κατέχει 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 1.10; ἐπ᾽ ἄκρᾳ τῇ φ. τῆς θαλάττης 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 16.19. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>frost, chill,</b> φ. περὶ τὸν ὄρθρον γέγονε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Gellius, Aulus Grammaticus Latinus 17.8.7. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9662","accentedUnicode":"φρίκη","shortDef":"shuddering awe","mediumDef":"shuddering awe","stepGloss":"shuddering awe","stepTransliteration":"frikē","_step_Type":"word"}]}